body_content.explanation: to be more successful than someone or something:
examples: Two commodities have been able to outcompete all other goods.
Societies that do not organize themselves effectively are outcompeted by societies that do.

body_content.explanation: (of a type of plant or animal) to succeed in getting more food, space, etc. than another type of plant or animal:
examples: Shrubs seem to outcompete grass in dry times.
Mink have been wiping out waterfowl and outcompeting the native otter.
